#: ../../S/snail-mail.rst:5
msgid "snail-mail"
msgstr "snail-mail"

#: ../../S/snail-mail.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../S/snail-mail.rst:9
msgid ""
"Paper mail, as opposed to electronic. Sometimes written as the single word "
"‘SnailMail’. One's postal address is, correspondingly, a snail address. "
"Derives from earlier coinage ‘USnail’ (from ‘U.S. Mail’), for which there "
"have even been parody posters and stamps made. Also (less commonly) called "
"P-mail, from ‘paper mail’ or ‘physical mail’. Oppose :ref:`email`\\."
msgstr ""
"電子メールに対する、紙のメール。‘SnailMail’と一語で書かれることもある。それに応じて、自分の郵便の住所はsnail "
"address(かたつむり住所)である。より早い造語‘USnail’(‘U.S. "
"Mail’から)に由来し、それにはパロディのポスターや切手まで作られている。また(あまり一般的ではないが)‘paper mail’や‘physical "
"mail’からP-mailとも呼ばれる。\\ :ref:`email`\\ と対比せよ。"

#: ../../S/snail-mail.rst:17
msgid ""
"(Note: Actual garden snails progress at about 10 meters per hour, which is "
"about 25-50 times slower than the U.K.'s Royal Mail; comparable measurements"
" for other countries have not yet been made. More biologically apt terms "
"might be \"sloth-mail\" at 250 m/hr or \"tortoise-mail\" at 270 m/hr. See "
"`http://www.newscientist.com/lastword/answers/789communication.jsp?tp=communication"
" "
"<http://www.newscientist.com/lastword/answers/789communication.jsp?tp=communication>`_\\"
"  for details.)"
msgstr ""
"(注: 実際の庭のかたつむりは時速約10メートルで進む。これは英国のRoyal "
"Mailより約25〜50倍遅い。他の国についての同等の測定はまだなされていない。生物学的により的確な用語は、時速250メートルの「sloth-"
"mail(なまけもの便)」や、時速270メートルの「tortoise-mail(りくがめ便)」だろう。詳細は\\ "
"`http://www.newscientist.com/lastword/answers/789communication.jsp?tp=communication"
" "
"<http://www.newscientist.com/lastword/answers/789communication.jsp?tp=communication>`_\\"
" を参照。)"
